SIMPLE: deafening
RECORDS: 2

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: deafening
<hw>deaf"en*ing</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>The act or process of rendering
impervious to sound, as a floor or wall; also, the material with which
the spaces are filled in this process; pugging; sound
insulation.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>deafening</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: deafening
<hw>deaf"en*ing</hw>, <pos>a.</pos> <def>extremely loud; so loud as to
cause deafness; <as>as, a disco with rock music played at a
<ex>deafening</ex> volume</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Deafly</ent>⟦br⟧
